Amos TACKETT, Appellant, v. Anthony J. CELEBREZZE, Secretary of Health, Education and Welfare, Appellee. No. 10096. United States Court of Appeals Fourth Circuit. Argued Jan. 3, 1966. Decided Jan. 10, 1966. Hugh P. Cline, Norton, Va., (Cline & McAfee, Norton, Va., on brief), for appellant. Harvey L. Zuckman, Atty., Dept, of Justice (John W. Douglas, Asst. Atty. Gen., and Sherman L. Cohn, Atty., Dept, of Justice, and Thomas B. Mason, U. S. Atty., on brief), for appellee.

Before HAYNSWORTH, Chief Judge, and SOBELOFF and BRYAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM:

In this proceeding for disability benefits under the Social Security Act, we find substantial evidence supporting the Secretary’s decision.

Affirmed.
